evidence: To keep a record of your session, use the diary command: diary filename x = 3 diary off
This will keep a diary called filename showing the value of x (your work for this session).
Timing: Use tic, toc to determine the running time of an algorithm as follows: tic commands... toc
This will give the elapsed time.

concepts.term: keep a record of your work
measure how long your code takes to run

evidence: Start with diary followed by a filename. From that point on, everything you type and everything MATLAB prints will be saved in a log file.
If you want to measure how long your code takes to run, just put tic before the commands, and toc after them.
This helps you compare different methods and optimize performance.
